HEADWORD: Gaff-topsail
<hw>Gaff`-top"sail</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A small triangular sail having its foot extended upon the gaff and
its luff upon the topmast.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

